==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trinodal
<hw>Tri*nod"al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>trinodis</ets> three-knotted; <ets>tri-</ets> (see <er>Tri-</er>) +
<ets>nodus</ets> knot.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having
three knots or nodes; having three points from which a leaf may shoot;
<as>as, a <ex>trinodal</ex> stem</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Geom.)</fld> <def>Having three nodal
points.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trinomial</ent>⟦br⟧
